{"id": "EUVD-2022-55724", "enisaUuid": "d4b7d2b6-4319-3a4e-a580-3a7b9a3ac135", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrivers: perf: marvell_cn10k: Fix hotplug callback leak in tad_pmu_init()\n\ntad_pmu_init() won't remove the callback added by cpuhp_setup_state_multi()\nwhen platform_driver_register() failed. Remove the callback by\ncpuhp_remove_multi_state() in fail path.\n\nSimilar to the handling of arm_ccn_init() in commit 26242b330093 (\"bus:\narm-ccn: Prevent hotplug callback leak\")", "datePublished": "2025-12-09T03:31:08", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-09T03:31:08", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/367404bfd1aa87b2a50059cd8edc6c12c367cd15", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7772f4de934123ccd7c7cdc1dc4e46fdd5d767fb", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/973ae93d80d9d262f695eb485a1902b74c4b9098", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50632"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50632"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0d0db9e4-3686-371a-bd9a-03b1e4d290d7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2"}, {"id": "1512cfaf-81c2-30b2-b21b-a5820059eb81", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "036a7584bede317d0df6b854e4f531b7a2dd8b33 <973ae93d80d9d262f695eb485a1902b74c4b9098"}, {"id": "180da6a7-9cf4-3783-86ec-2d678cfda44b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0.16"}, {"id": "83282b1b-2d34-33f9-9f5f-9b97fb48529d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "036a7584bede317d0df6b854e4f531b7a2dd8b33 <367404bfd1aa87b2a50059cd8edc6c12c367cd15"}, {"id": "bd0c47e3-f704-38bd-b708-f47c04f9f5f1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.17"}, {"id": "db99f2d7-3aad-300d-ae0a-c57312ad4ed7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.2"}, {"id": "e5ce0705-d93f-304f-99d5-18060cfa03a0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "036a7584bede317d0df6b854e4f531b7a2dd8b33 <7772f4de934123ccd7c7cdc1dc4e46